Title: People v. Williams
HTMLtext:
725 N.W.2d 348 (2007)

PEOPLE of the State of Michigan, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Jimmie Lee WILLIAMS, Defendant-Appellant.

Docket No. 132372. COA No. 272831.

Supreme Court of Michigan.

January 4, 2007.

On order of the Court, the application for leave to appeal the October 18, 2006 order of the Court of Appeals is considered, and it is DENIED, because the defendant's motion for relief from judgment is prohibited by MCR 6.502(G).
